gomodel:SYNGO_2559  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"Electron micrographs demonstrating the subcellular localization of m3 receptor protein\"\n- \"D, m4-positive spiny dendrite (d). Asymmetrical synapses (arrows) are present on the dendritic shaft and spine head (3). Note the concentration of r reaction product in the spine neck and at the postsynaptic densities. E, Higher-magnification view of a large m4-immunoreactive spine (s) with apparent accumulation of reaction product at the postsynaptic densities (arrows).\"\n\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: \"Twelve young adult male Sprague-Dawley (Harlan) rats were deeply anesthetized ...\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
